x4freetext: MEASUREMENT OF NEUTRON FISSION CROSS SECTIONS OF
TWO PARALLEL PLATE IONIZATION CHAMBERS WITH 25
PERCENT ENRICHED BF(3) AND 75 PERCENT ARGON AT 75
CM MERCURY PRESSURE. EACH DETECTOR IS 2.5 CM THICK.
ONE CHAMBER WAS PLACED AT 20.5 M TO MONITOR THE
NEUTRON FLUX AND THE OTHER ALTERNATED WITH THE
A FOUR PART FISSION CHAMBER WITH A COATED PLATE
AND AN UNCOATED COLLECTOR PLATE SEPARATED BY 0.3 CM
IN EACH SECTION. EACH SECTION WAS ISOLATED BY 0.001
CM THICK ALUMINUM PLATES. THE CHAMBER WAS FILLED
WITH A GAS 90 PERCENT ARGON AND 10 PERCENT METHANE.
DATA ARE CORRECTED FOR DEAD TIME, CONSTANT AND TIME-
DATA SHOULD BE USED WITH CAUTION ABOVE 20 EV.
DATA RECEIVED IN PRIVATE COMMUNICATION 86/7/31 FROM
SAMPLE WAS COATED 1 TO 1.4 G/M**2 AND 7.6 CM DIAMETER
ON ALUMINUM DISKS 10 CM DIAMETER AND 0.001 CM THICK.
